Vice President Mike Pence delivered a speech at the BWI Airport Marriott in Linthicum Heights, Maryland, emphasizing the accomplishments of the Trump administration and the need for four more years of President Donald Trump. Pence highlighted the strong economy, job growth, tax cuts, and efforts to rebuild the military and secure the southern border. He also criticized the Democrats' push for socialism and defended the sanctity of human life. Pence called on fellow Republicans to take their message to all Americans and have faith in the American people's choice for more freedom. He encouraged prayer for the nation's prosperity and security. Pence concluded by expressing optimism and the belief that with continued support and strong Republican leadership, America will be safe, prosperous, and greater than ever before.